  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BitVector, it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.booleans.BooleanCollection, it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.booleans.BooleanIterable, it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.booleans.BooleanList, it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.booleans.BooleanStack, it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.Stack<Boolean>, Serializable, Comparable<List<? extends Boolean>>, Iterable<Boolean>, Collection<Boolean>, List<Boolean>, RandomAccess

    public class BooleanListBitVector
extends AbstractBitVector
implements Serializable
    A boolean-list based implementation of BitVector.

    This implementation of a bit vector is based on a backing list of booleans. It is rather inefficient, but useful for wrapping purposes, for covering completely the code in AbstractBitVector and for creating mock objects.
